            <div type="a">
                <column>03</column>
                <head>Speech of Horatio Seymour</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Much of the front page is devoted to the speech of the Democratic
                    presidential candidate Horatio Seymour delivered at New York's Cooper Institute.
                    He denounces the debt, high taxes, extravagance and corruption accompanying
                    Republican rule.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
        <page n="02" image="pa.fr.vs.1868.09.09.02" exists="no">
            <div type="e">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>John Cessna</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper denounces Republican congressional candidate John Cessna's "low
                    and vulgar speech" delivered in the Court House in which he attacked the editors
                    of the Valley Spirit. Even Republican Party members were appalled, according to
                    the paper.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
