            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>The County Fair</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Gilbert</ln>
                        <fn>Calvin</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Skinner</ln>
                        <fn>Wash.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Capt.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Preparations for the fair are almost complete. The stalls and sheds are
                    "substantial" and perfect for the care and protection of the livestock. Entries
                    can be placed with the Secretary Calvin Gilbert of Chambersburg. Hay and straw
                    will be furnished for free. Only the time trials and tournament have entry fees.
                    Capt. Wash. Skinner's new militia company will give a military display.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
