                </names>
                <summary>The White Boys in Blue held a meeting in Gelwick's building at which they
                    selected officers. J. L. P. Detrich was chosen Chairman; Capt. George W.
                    Skinner, President; Sergt. David Hissong, Vice President; Philip Loudenslager,
                    Vice President; J. L. P. Detrich, Recording Secretary; D. M. Sheller,
                    Corresponding Secretary. Capt. Skinner "made a short address, giving the reasons
                    why soldiers who fought for the Union and the Constitution should now vote to
                    sustain the principles for which they had risked their lives." A committee was
                    appointed to form a Glee Club in conjunction with the Seymour and Blair Club.
                    Many soldiers joined.</summary>
                <note/>
