                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Cessna</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>The Republicans of Chambersburg held a well-attended meeting in the Court
                    House. According to the Spirit, Isaac H. McCauley's speech was rife with factual
                    errors about Republican progress in reducing the debt. The editors assert that
                    John Cessna's speech alienated many voters for its vulgar attack on the Valley
                    Spirit. He called the editors "tom-tits," "tumblebugs," and "skunks."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
