                <summary>Snively Strickler, member of the Franklin County Bar and once proprietor of
                    the Repository, died suddenly at his Greencastle residence. He was a native of
                    Antrim. The Franklin County Bar passed resolutions of sympathy and attended the
                    funeral in Greencastle. Strickler was buried in the Lutheran cemetery. The
                    lawyers thank O. N. Lull, Superintendent of the Cumberland Valley Railroad, for
                    allowing them to ride to Greencastle free of charge.</summary>
                <note/>
