                <summary>The Democratic Congressional Conference for the 16th District, that
                    includes Franklin, met to nominate a candidate. F. M. Kimmell of Franklin was
                    nominated on the 46th ballot. The conferees passed resolutions endorsing the
                    Johnson administrations "efforts to maintain the constitutional authority of the
                    government against the usurpations and innovations of a partisan mob," and
                    supporting Horatio Seymour for president.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
